        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <figure id="f9912091" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9912091.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Engine Vertical Air Intake Pipe Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9912091">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                and part numbers listed in the table.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Evaluate the engine vertical air intake pipe assembly for fatigue and replace as
                    required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Use a depth stop on the drill bit when performing the next step to prevent damage to the
                        muffler.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drill the 7/16 inch support bracket mounting holes in the muffler bracket taking care
                    not to hit the muffler. Use the support bracket or the template in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9912092">Figure 2</hotlnk>
                    as a hole location guide.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the support bracket to the muffler bracket with 3/8-16 x 1 inch bolts, nuts,
                    lock washers and flat washers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the support clamp kit following the instructions provided with the kit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the support clamp bolt to 12 ft-lbs.(16 Nm) max torque.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Do not exceed 12 ft-lbs. (16 Nm) tightening torque to prevent the support clamp bolt from
                            failing.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="f9912092" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9912092.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. Mounting Bracket Template</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
